OL,3,CMan guilty of murdering and
OL,4,Cdismembering housemate
OL,6,FThe Crown Prosecution Service (CPS)
OL,7,Fdescribed the crime as "barbaric" and
OL,8,Fsaid there was "overwhelming evidence"
OL,9,FMajerkiewicz carried out the crime.
OL,11,FRebecca Macaulay-Addison, Specialist
OL,12,FProsecutor for CPS North West's
OL,13,FComplex Casework Unit, said: "Marcin
OL,14,FMajerkiewicz murdered Stuart Everett
OL,15,Fbefore making a despicable and
OL,16,Fdisturbing attempt to cover his tracks
OL,17,Fby disposing of Mr Everett's remains.
OL,26,@uD@^OU
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G9/13
