OL,3,CMan guilty of murdering and
OL,4,Cdismembering housemate
OL,6,F"He went on to concoct a web of lies
OL,7,Fto further conceal his barbaric crime.
OL,8,FHe assumed Mr Everett's identity, sent
OL,9,Fmessages to others claiming he had
OL,10,Fsuffered a stroke and was
OL,11,Fhospitalised, and even sent a
OL,12,Fhandwritten birthday card to Mr
OL,13,FEverett's brother, all to give the
OL,14,Fimpression that Mr Everett was still
OL,15,Falive.
OL,17,F"Majerkiewicz not only stole a loved
OL,18,Fone from those who cared for Mr
OL,19,FEverett - his subsequent actions are
OL,20,Falmost certain to have compounded
OL,21,Ftheir pain and suffering.
OL,26,@nD@AOUyD@AOU
